<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_EP21_ProjectGold_FoundingADynasty" s="488444">
  <T n="category">488441<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_Category_EP21_ProjectGold--></T>
  <T n="name">0x22C94A25<!--String: "Founding & Joining a Dynasty"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_FoundDynasty1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5730f3c50822946b</T>
      <T n="text">0xA26FCBCA<!--String: "For Sims who want to <b><font color='#199C2C'>unite their family</font></b> to achieve success and create a lasting legacy, founding or joining a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Dynasty</font></b> is a must! It will allow them to align on shared <b><font color='#199C2C'>Values</font></b>, build <b><font color='#199C2C'>Prestige</font></b>, and unlock powerful <b><font color='#199C2C'>Perks</font></b> and relationship bonuses.\n\nThe main way to found a new Dynasty is via the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Dynasty tab of the Social Groups menu</font></b>, but there are also other ways to found or join a Dynasty, for example by <b><font color='#199C2C'>marrying</font></b> into one, or <b><font color='#199C2C'>forging a family connection</font></b>.\n\nThe founder of a new Dynasty becomes the first <b><font color='#199C2C'>Dynasty Head</font></b>. They will choose the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Dynasty name, Crest, description, and Values</font></b>. The Values are the heart of a Dynasty; you can read more about them in the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Dynasty Values Lesson</font></b>."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_FoundDynasty2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5730f3c508229468</T>
      <T n="text">0xC7F79C4D<!--String: "To join a Dynasty, a Sim must be connected to it by certain <b><font color='#199C2C'>family ties</font></b>. All close relations of the Head may join, as may spouses, children, and grandchildren of other Members. Spouses, blood relatives, and step relatives are all eligible, however in laws are not.\n\nA Dynasty Head can <b><font color='#199C2C'>invite</font></b> Sims via the Dynasty Menu or an interaction in the Dynasty Social category. Sims who are not yet members may also <b><font color='#199C2C'>ask the Head to be invited</font></b>. Newborns can be added to a Dynasty on <b><font color='#199C2C'>birth</font></b>.\n\nRemember, an invite or request for invitation can be <b><font color='#199C2C'>turned down</font></b>! Improving the relationship may lead to a yes, but some Sims may also be a terrible fit if their Traits conflict strongly with the Dynasty Values."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_FoundDynasty3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5730f3c508229469</T>
      <T n="text">0xD45D6D2F<!--String: "A Dynasty Member can create a new <b><font color='#199C2C'>off-shoot Dynasty</font></b> by selecting Found a Dynasty in the Dynasty Settings, and two Sims from different Dynasties can found a new blended Dynasty upon <b><font color='#199C2C'>marriage</font></b>.\n\nThis new Dynasty will have a starting Prestige Level based on that of the original Dynasty (or Dynasties). \n\nBe careful though; creating a new Dynasty and poaching members from the original one may cause <b><font color='#199C2C'>conflict</font></b>! Or perhaps conflict is just what the new Head has in mind…"--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
